Tricky Question
Why not use @Transactional across services?
 Because distributed transactions reduce scalability and are failure-prone.


ğŸ”¹ SECTION 5: FAULT TOLERANCE & RESILIENCE

how do you handle failure?

pattern: circuit breaker, retry, timeout, fallback

tools: resilence4j

Retry always good?
Answer
No. Retrying can overload a failing service (retry storm).

Circuit Breaker States
State	Meaning
CLOSED	Normal
OPEN	Stop calls
HALF-OPEN	Trial calls

ğŸ”¹ SECTION 6: SECURITY

how is scurity implemented?

